text: Christopher John Guelph Puplick (born 13 May 1948) is an Australian politician. He is a member of the Liberal Party. He served as a Senator for New South Wales from 1978 to 1981, and then again from 1984 to 1990. Puplick was born in London, United Kingdom. His family moved to Sydney, New South Wales in 1962. He was married to Francesca Muir until their divorce. ==References== Category:1948 births Category:Living people Category:Liberal Party of Australia politicians Category:Members of the Australian Senate Category:Order of Australia Category:Politicians from London Category:Politicians from Sydney
